  "response_text": "A dusty, animated desert training camp comes into view as the back of an old gray bus drives forward between crooked fence posts and dry scrub. Through the small rear window of the bus, rounded fruit characters can be seen inside. The bus passes under a large wooden arch with bold white letters reading “FRUIT CAMP,” with lamps hanging above it and watchtowers and low camp buildings in the distance.\n\nThe bus stops beside a camp area, and a line of anthropomorphic fruit characters stands outside it like recruits. They have cartoon faces, thin black arms and legs, and little boots. Among them are an orange, a pear, a banana, a green apple, a lemon, a raspberry-like red fruit, a pineapple, and other small fruit characters. In front of them stands the leader: a tall red twisted fruit-snack character with a yellow spiral stripe wrapped around his body, long black limbs, gloves, oversized black boots, and a wide-brimmed drill-sergeant-style hat. His face is stern, with heavy-lidded eyes and a big rectangular mouth full of white teeth.\n\nThe red twist character strides in front of the recruits, gesturing with a long black pointer or baton. He holds up a bright yellow-and-red Kellogg’s Fruit Twistables box so the front faces outward. The package has the large blue “Fruit Twistables” logo across it and pictures of twisted fruit-snack strips near the bottom. He points at the box while addressing the fruit lineup, using exaggerated arm movements and leaning forward with a commanding expression.\n\nThe recruits react nervously. A pale yellow pear with a stem on top stares wide-eyed, its mouth open in worry, while an orange beside it looks uneasy. The red twist character paces close in front of them, his long limbs and pointer crossing the foreground. The pear squeezes its eyes shut as if bracing itself, then opens them again with a startled look.\n\nThe scene widens to show the whole line beside the bus. The red twist leader looms over the smaller fruit characters, holding the Fruit Twistables box and baton. A yellow lemon near the line is chewing or blowing a pink bubble. The bubble grows large in front of the lemon’s face, and the red twist leader moves past with the baton. The pink bubble bursts or collapses, leaving the lemon’s face and body splattered with pink goo. The nearby green apple, with a leaf on its stem, looks on with round eyes.\n\nThe red twist leader leans in close to the lemon, his face filling the view beside the lemon’s yellow surface. He raises the baton and scowls, baring his teeth as he appears to scold the lemon. The lemon is left coated in pink patches, its eyes drooping in embarrassment or defeat.\n\nBack in the lineup, the goo-covered lemon stands beside a small red raspberry-like fruit and a tall peeled banana. The red twist leader marches past them, boots thudding through the dusty ground, while the banana watches with a nervous hand near its mouth. The wider camp setting remains visible: a gray bus behind the recruits, tan barracks, sparse desert plants, and guard towers under a bright sky.\n\nA tiny purple grape character wearing an oversized tan helmet stands between the larger fruits’ boots. The grape has a small face, thin arms and legs, and looks up anxiously as the red twist leader’s big boots move around it. The leader steps and pivots dramatically, carrying the Fruit Twistables box and baton, while the little grape remains directly in the path of the action.\n\nThe red twist leader then performs an exaggerated demonstration, stretching and twisting his red-and-yellow body as if showing off the product’s “twist” theme. He leans far back, flips his hat upward, and bends his flexible body in big arcs while still holding the package. The fruit recruits watch from the side, including the tall banana, pineapple, lemon, apple, and raspberry. At one point, a huge boot sole fills the view from below, emphasizing how close the leader’s foot comes to the tiny grape.\n\nThe grape reappears flattened into a shiny purple splat on a wooden crate or platform, with bits of the tan helmet and purple droplets around it. Even flattened, the grape’s cartoon face remains visible in the gooey purple puddle, giving a comic impression that it is still conscious.\n\nThe red twist leader stands tall again in front of the lined-up fruit recruits, holding the baton horizontally like a command stick. The fruits stand at attention beside the bus: the orange and pear on the left, then the apple, goo-covered lemon, banana, pineapple, and small red fruits on the right. When the leader gives the final command, the fruit characters break formation and begin running in a chaotic rush. The orange and pear dash past the bus, while others scramble in different directions, kicking up dust.\n\nThe commercial ends with a product display in the same camp setting. Three large Kellogg’s Fruit Twistables boxes stand upright across the dusty ground, each with the big blue “Fruit Twistables” logo and colorful fruit-snack imagery on the front. The red twist drill sergeant pops up in front of the boxes, animatedly gesturing with his gloved hands and baton. He leans toward the viewer, smiles broadly, points forward, and holds his pose between the bright packages, reinforcing the product as the final visual focus.",
